snippet.description:

Following is a quote from Nancy (Scooter) McMoneagle, The Monroe Institute (TMI) President & Executive Director.  Scooter is also the stepdaughter of consciousness pioneer, Robert Monroe.

Spirituality references the meta-physical—that which goes beyond the material, mundane world; it includes a conscious sense of that which is greater than the individual, egocentric self, and embraces a connection to a unifying principal—an “All That Is.” 
Spirituality is about how we perceive, connect with, and bring this greater unifying principal into our lives. 
It is about consciously living from a more transcendent space of love, gratitude, kindness, compassion, nonjudgement, inclusiveness, respect and honor for all beings, resulting in a perception and experience of the profound sanctity and interconnectedness in all of life.

snippet.title: You are a Self Programmable Quantum Computer 2017 11 15
snippet.description:
Quantum computers are now commercially available with 2,000 qubits. The number of qubits in this technology seems to be increasing exponentially.  

Humans have about 37 trillion cells, give or take a few trillion.  The nucleus of each cell may be like a qubit in a quantum computer.  The human quantum computer seems to use microtubules to entangle the nodes into one integrated quantum computer.

Our ability to be precognitive is a good demonstration of our quantum capabilities, especially being non-local and able to gather info from the linear-future.  We have learned to do fantastic things, such as walk and talk, and we are therefore self-programmable quantum computers...and that is magnificent!

We also did a FeedBack Session for an earlier ARV prediction.

 ... what matters is not experience per se but "effortful study," which entails continually tackling challenges that lie just beyond one's competence.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: DisplacementCanBeYourFriend
snippet.description:
Group1ARV is an advanced form of Associative Remote Viewing.  The old fashioned Binary ARV approach suffered from Displacement, where an excellent description would be provided by the viewer of the wrong target ... a target that the viewer would never see.

In this  video, from a weekly free webinar, we describe the Group1ARV approach that permits displacement to assist the Analyst/Judge in providing a higher Hit Rate for precognitive predictions.  We also discuss the latest Hit Rates, which are currently at 68% with odds against chance of 2835 to 1.

Since we publicly presented our goal of a 80% long-term Hit Rate at the IRVA (International Remote Viewing Association) Conference, our 5 groups have had a 79% success rate.
